So, uh, let's explore the concept of dharma in, you know, the Mahabharata.

2
00:00:05,500 --> 00:00:10,000
Um, dharma literally means, er, that which upholds or sustains.

3
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:15,000
In chapter eighteen verse sixty six, Krishna says, actually, abandon all dharmas.

4
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:20,000
This is, like, one of the most profound statements in the entire Gita.

5
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:25,000
The Sanskrit term used here is, uh, sarva dharman parityajya.

6
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:30,000
It means, you know, give up all duties and surrender to me alone.

7
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:35,000
This teaching appears in the eighteenth chapter, verses sixty five to sixty six.

8
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:40,000
Actually, these verses are considered, er, the essence of the entire Bhagavad Gita.